<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 06-12-23 - Repair Guidelines for Horton DriveMaster Fan Clutches Installed on Vehicles Starting
        06/01/2000
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi061223" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>06-12-23</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>November, 2006</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Repair Guidelines for Horton DriveMaster Fan Clutches Installed on Vehicles Starting 06/01/2000
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="no" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Horton</vendor>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>To properly repair a Horton DriveMaster fan clutch the following guidelines should be used:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Liner Failure</emph>- use Friction Liner Kit 994349
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Friction Disc and Liner Failure</emph>- use Friction Disc Kit (see Chart)
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Seal and/or Air Cartridge</emph>- use Minor Seal Kit 994346
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Magnet Failure (Two Speed)</emph>- use Magnet Kit 994967
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Bearing Failure</emph>- use Bearing Kit (see Chart)
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Clutch Pack Failure</emph>- use Clutch Pack Kit (see Chart)
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Multiple Component Failures</emph>- use any combination of the above kits
                            and in the case of liner, friction disc, clutch pack and bearing failures use DriveMaster
                            Super Kit (see Chart).
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="bold">Clutch or fan Bracket, Cummins ISX</emph>- if there is a clutch or fan
                            bracket failure for a Cummins ISX engine built prior to October 1, 2006, with the old design
                            fan bracket (Figure 1), the clutch should
                            <emph type="bold">not</emph>
                            be repaired but replaced with a new or reman fan clutch
                        </para>
                        <para>When the vehicle is built with the new design fan bracket (Figure 2), the clutch can be
                            repaired with the kits listed in the Chart.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <para>During repairs all M12 flange head fasteners must be torqued to 80 to 100 Lbf-ft (108 to 136 Nm),
                    unless otherwise indicated.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Refer to the Horton web site (www.hortonww.com) for all additional information, such as:
                            repair kit descriptions, kit contents, fan clutch diagrams, and exploded views.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f0612231" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0612231.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="256px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Old Design Bracket for Cummins ISX</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0612232" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0612232.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. New Design for Cummins ISX</caption>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, allow the engine to cool sufficiently
                        before servicing the fan clutch.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Attached is a listing of the Horton&#174; DriveMaster kits available. To order these kits
                        through the International&#174; parts system, add the prefix "HOR" to the number for parts in
                        the Parts Distribution Center (PDC) or add the prefix "ZBH" to the part number for Direct Ship.
                    </para>
                    <para>You may refer to the Horton web site catalog at www.hortonww.com for the latest application
                        information to determine the correct kit for each application.
                    </para>
                    <para>Please contact your local Horton representative or the Customer Support Department at
                        1-800-621-1320 for more information or to place an order.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
